description: For sale: $349,900. Huge twinhome with a nice backyard and big storage shed.  2 master suites, with one on the main level and one in the basement. Feels like a single-family home in a great location, close to the MOA and freeways.  Hard to find this amount of square footage for the price!

For sale: $325,000. Welcome home to this exceptionally updated rambler. Turn the key & step into your new dream home! Note the gorgeous refinished hardwood floors that lead to a modern kitchen remodel w/granite counter tops, stainless appliances w/double oven, touch-less faucet, and open concept main floor living. Floor plan opens into a combined living/dining area accented by beautiful lighting. Smart Lutron Caseta recessed dimmers throughout plus a wifi controlled thermostat. Upper level features a fresh full bath remodel w/custom subway tile surround. 2 spacious main floor beds nearby. Exterior boasts maintenance free siding, newer roof, and gutters in a fenced yard with green space behind. Patio space and ample driveway parking lead to an insulated 2 car garage/man cave w/ heat options. Owners made the LL a master en-suite w/heated tile floors bath, w/in custom shower & closet. New carpet and padding accent the LL FR. Remote office space & storage too! Virtual Tour & home highlight links.

For sale: $250,000. RARE opportunity in East Bloomington! Absolutely charming vintage home with hard to find oversized. .82 lot in downtown Bloomington. Tons of possibilities with ownership of this size lot. Spectacular lot to have your own park like setting! Clean and charming spaces will win you over. Great wood flooring through out, 2 bathrooms, newer boiler, new kitchen appliances. home right in the heart of downtown Bloomington. Location is hard to beat! Walk to everything or take the bus wherever you need to go.

description: Recently sold: $245,752. This gorgeous 3 Bedroom, 2 Bathroom home is completely remodeled!  Beautifully updated Kitchen with new stainless-steel appliances, new granite counter tops, new trim, and fresh paint. Spacious sun filled Living Room with  re-finished oak hardwood flooring. The Main Level Full Bathroom has been completely renovated! New vinyl flooring, a new vanity The 2 Bedrooms located on the main level both feature refinished oak hardwood flooring, fresh paint, and new trim. The lower level Family Room has new carpet, new trim, and fresh paint. This is the perfect spot for a movie or game night! Bedroom 3 and the 3/4 bathroom in the lower level were recently added, everything is brand new! New doors, new furnace, new air conditioner, new water heater, new electrical, new plumbing, and a new garage floor! Enjoy maintenance free living! Main floor laundry, bedroom and eat-in kitchen are just a few of the features you will find.

Recently sold: $319,900. Welcome Home! This lovely Rambler has many Amenities! Granite, black SSappliances, main floor master with a large walk-in-closet and built-ins. Walk out to the beautiful patio with a permanentnatural gas outdoor BBQ, great for grilling and entertaining! Enjoy yourcoffee overlooking the pristine gardens and landscaping! description: Recently sold: $288,500. Bright and spacious home with with main floor Master with ensuite bath, walk-in closet and fireplace. Easy walking to Pleasant Playlot, Gene C. Kelly Playfields, and many river trails through Mound Springs Park and more!

description:
Recently sold: $248,000. Location! Location! Location! Easy access to 35W, 494, and 77 on quiet street across from a park. Retro property in perfect condition! Wake up to sunshine as this home has great windows with lots of natural light. Built-in hutch in dining room, wood floors on entire main floor. Partially fenced in back yard with garden area and oversized double car garage. Gather a bouquet of lilacs in the spring from your yard. Basement finished with laundry area, 1/2 bath and large rec room. It even has a cedar closet and extra freezer! One small dog under 20 lbs ok with additional security deposit of $250.00 and increased rent of $25/month. Will need to meet this wonderful pet of yours before approval of lease. This is a one of a kind property that you don't want to miss!

Tenant pays all utilities, mows the lawn and shovels the snow.

description:
Recently sold: $420,000. MAIN LEVEL

Living Room
Welcoming you into the home is a large tiled foyer and a bright and spacious living room. The living room has a completely open concept to the kitchen and informal dining area. It boasts a see through double-sided tiled gas fireplace, recessed lighting, gorgeous large windows surrounding the entire living room and double door walk-outs to the 3-season porch.

Kitchen
This kitchen is a chef?s dream! Open to the both the informal dining room and living room ? the kitchen lacks no detail. It contains a massive granite center island, top of the line stainless steel appliances, plenty of storage, recessed lighting, ice machine, warming drawer, beverage cooler, and tiled backsplash!

Informal Dining Room
The informal dining room is an open area to the kitchen and living room with tall windows and a door walking out to the three-season porch.

Three-Season Porch
The three-season porch is the perfect place to relax or entertain. It is surrounded by floor-to-ceiling windows and doors, completely tiled floor, an artistically thought out tiled double sided see through gas fireplace, and a walk-out to an additional attached deck that includes a natural gas weber barbecue making for a great picnic area! 

Mid-Level Family Room
Walk down a few steps and you will find the mid-level family room containing another fireplace with brick surround and a walk-out to the pool area. Adjacent to the family room is also a ¾ tiled bathroom with a fully tiled shower.

Mid-Level Bedroom 3
This mid-level bedroom has plush carpet, a large closet, a large egress window, and ceiling fan.

UPPER LEVEL

Master Bedroom 
The master bedroom is an amazing retreat. It has massive patio doors along the walls, two huge walk-in closets, a walk-out to a deck/hot tub area, recessed lighting, and a connected private master suite bathroom. The master bathroom is beautifully done with tile from floor to ceiling, double sinks, contemporary deep soaking tub and separate shower area with a waterfall shower and a separate toilet area!
Bedroom 2
This bedroom has gorgeous hardwood floors, a large closet, and two patio sliding doors to access the pool, balcony, deck, and hot tub. It also has its own private ¾ tiled bathroom with a heavy glass door and a floor-to-ceiling tile shower.

LOWER LEVEL
Family Room 
The lower level family room is a great place to get away and use the massive theatre screen. It comes complete with surround sound and 120? projector screen. All you need is the projector! The family room also has carpet, a large storage room, and an access to the garage.



Additional Features:

?	38? x 20? Custom Concrete Pool w/ All the Bells & Whistles
?	Custom Pool House w/ Changing Room & Huge Sauna
?	2006 Sundance Hot Tub
?	ADT Security System
?	Horseshoe Driveway
?	Furnace Humidifier
?	Multiple Large Decks & Patios
?	New Windows, French, and Sliding Doors Throughout
?	Front Privacy Composite Fence w/Security Gate
?	Backyard Fence for Total Privacy

description: Recently sold: $262,500. This is a well-built home from the mid-1950s. This home is a rambler that features 3 bedrooms and a full bath on the main level, with 1 bedroom & 3/4 bathroom in basement. A large family room w/ fireplace and the basement BR were added to the back of the home in the late 1960s. The pass-through garage and outdoor shed were built around the same time. Two fireplaces adorn the main floor family/living rooms, with the newer fireplace now modified for use with an energy-efficient wood-burning insert. Improvements have been made over time, with the most recent face-lift performed in 2013 as refinished HW floors and fresh coats of paint throughout the main floor. One of unique features of this house is an extra-deep (or tall) basement. The foundation was built with additional block courses, which is typically not the case in 50s era homes. Outdoor space is plentiful, and the backyard features a deck, a large garden space, and space for future changes/upgrades (i.e. patio or landscaping). Mature trees provide great cover from the summer heat which results in less energy use for cooling. Overall, this is a fantastic home in a great East Bloomington neighborhood.
